      {
        "id": "A",
        "text": "Q4 revenue is more than double Q1 revenue"
      },
      {
        "id": "B",
        "text": "Total annual revenue exceeds $100,000"
      },
      {
        "id": "C",
        "text": "Q3 revenue is the lowest of the year"
      },
      {
        "id": "D",
        "text": "The average quarterly revenue is $30,000"
      }
    ],
    "answer": [
      "A",
      "B",
      "D"
    ],
    "solutionStandard": "(A) \\(45000 > 2\\times20000=40000\\), true. (B) Total \\(=20000+30000+25000+45000=120000 > 100000\\), true. (C) Q1 ($20,000) is actually the lowest, not Q3 ($25,000), so false. (D) Average \\(=120000/4=30000\\), true.",
    "timeTargetSec": 90
  },
